<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="223" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1327,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,374,1543,1568]" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">Measurements</emphasis>
. Total length 17.2–17.7; total width 9.4–9.8; head length 1.5–1.7; head width 2.9–3.1; length of antennal articles I: 0.7–1.0; II: 1.8–1.9; III: 1.2–1.6; IV: 3.0–3.2; pronotum length 3.1–3.3; pronotum width 9.9– 10.1; scutellum length 7.7–8.1; scutellum width 5.8–6.0.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="18" pageNumber="223" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1327,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1652,1677]" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species medium (
<quantity box="[552,668,1652,1676]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="18" pageNumber="223" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="17.0">17–18mm</quantity>
) and dorsally green. Pronotum with brown to black punctures interspersed with irregular yellow lines or spots. Scutellum with large punctures on dark brown spots. Contour of the corium completely made by yellow veins like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fernandes &amp; Nascimento &amp; Nunes" authorityYear="2018" box="[733,843,1724,1748]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Pygoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="223" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="poecila">
<emphasis box="[733,843,1724,1748]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">P. poecila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; close to costal margin sometimes occur few (around 3) small calloused yellow spots and a rhombus (
<figureCitation box="[702,805,1759,1784]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Connexivum green with median yellow oblong callus (
<figureCitation box="[159,262,1796,1821]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); segment VII with basal half green and distal half black partially surrounding yellow median calloused spot. Body ventrally mostly greenish yellow or pale yellow with some parts light green, dark brown narrow lines on the edges of the sternites and pseudosutures. Evaporatorium brown. Antennae and legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1327,2037]" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">
Head. Mandibular plates with dense punctuation. Tylus yellow medially with margin dark (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1334,1903,1928]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface yellow. First rostral segment slightly surpassing bucculae in lateral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1327,2037]" lastBlockId="19.[151,1437,151,464]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="224" pageId="18" pageNumber="223">
Thorax. Pronotum densely punctured, punctures coarse; pronotal disc with small irregular yellow callus; cicatrices variegate with green and greenish yellow, delimiting dark furrows surrounded by pale greenish yellow calloused stripes (
<figureCitation box="[352,454,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">Fig. 13C</figureCitation>
); anterior delimiting furrow punctured. Anterolateral margin pale yellow; line of brown coarse punctures long, exceeding ½ of the margin. Anterolateral punctuated line short, reaching 1/3 of the anterolateral margin; punctures dark and coarse. Scutellum with coarse, large, black punctures sparser on anterior half and median longitudinal line than on remaining parts, lateral and distal punctures small, fine and black; most of the punctures on dark brown spots. Corium with few yellow veins branched and isolated yellow calli (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1423,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">Fig 13C</figureCitation>
). Propleura with dark stripe alongside dark, fine and dense punctures; green stripe parallel to yellow margin. Evaporatorium dark and rugose. Peritreme short reaching 1/3 of the distance between ostiole of the scent gland and margin of the body. Metasternal process greenish yellow with arms broad and receiving fourth rostral segment (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="224" startId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" targetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" targetPageId="19">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1435,1870,1923]" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1870,1892]" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">FIGURE 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Comb." baseAuthorityName="Breddin" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[281,425,1870,1892]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Pygoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="civilis">
<emphasis box="[281,425,1870,1892]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">Pygoda civilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,1962,2023]" lastBlockId="20.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="20" lastPageNumber="225" pageId="19" pageNumber="224">
Abdomen. Connexivum with excavations concolorous, densely punctured except on yellow callus and distal margin on each segment; base of lateral spines green. Lateral part of segment VII, corresponding to ventral side of connexivum, greenish yellow with margin partially black, sometimes only inner margin black. Yellow spot surrounding spiracles. Small brown rounded spot close to spiracle on each segment (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1202,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1029,1051]" captionTargetBox="[356,1227,204,950]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[309,1273,183,1024]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 13. Dorsal and ventral view. Pygoda expolita A–B; Pygoda civilis C–D; Pygoda thoracica E–F (Scale = 5mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460052/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">
Male (
<figureCitation box="[274,401,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A–C</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with posterolateral angles slightly flat laterally and little projected (
<figureCitation box="[1330,1423,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup rounded and large. Paramere with only two processes, posterior margin only with ventral, short and rounded process curved laterally, distal process absent; dorsal margin slightly enlarged and flat or barely excavated (
<figureCitation box="[371,467,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Proctiger dark brown with posterior face yellow, short, not reaching level of posterolateral angles (
<figureCitation box="[405,496,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
); lateral excavation barely forming a crest dorsally; dorsal part of posterior face tumid. Ventral rim medially greenish yellow or light yellow; expansions strongly developed and tumid (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface mostly greenish yellow or light yellow with few suffused dark spots; punctures fine and concolorous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">
Female (
<figureCitation box="[299,392,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1870,1892]" captionTargetBox="[243,1356,533,1826]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[213,1382,500,1866]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pygoda civilis. A–C Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—ventral view. D—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1460044/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). Gonocoxites 8 with lateral margin almost rounded and posterior margin black, arched or acuminated near laterotergites 9; punctures slightly concentrated on convex part; sutural border contiguous except distally; gonapophysis 8 not visible. Gonocoxites 9 large, distal part straight. Laterotergites 8 with black distal margin projected in a black spine that exceeds apex of segment VII. Laterotergites 9 with small part of the base excavated; apices below the level of laterotergites 8.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="225" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,692,717]" pageId="20" pageNumber="225">Comments.</emphasis>
The previously unknown female is recognized and described in this work. Male and female genitalia were not dissected.
</paragraph>
